    "##\n",
    "## subset the design matrix to eliminate the first column of 1s\n",
    "## the iloc method says to find the location of columns based on their integer locations (i.e., 0, 1, 2, etc.)\n",

    "## create the correlation matrix\n",
    "##\n",
    "x = reg01.model.data.orig_exog.iloc[ :, 1: ] \n",
    "corr_matrix = x.corr()\n",

    "##\n",
    "## regress GNPDEFL on GNP, UNEMP, ARMED, POP, YEAR\n",
    "##\n",
    "formula = 'GNPDEFL ~ GNP + UNEMP + ARMED + POP + YEAR'\n",
    "reg02 = smf.ols( formula, data = df ).fit()\n",
    "print( reg02.summary() )\n",
    "print( '\\n RSquared = ', round( reg02.rsquared, 3 ) )\n",
    "print( '\\n Tolerance = 1 - R2 = ', round( 1 - reg02.rsquared, 3 ) )\n",
    "print( '\\n VIF_GNPDEFL = 1/TOLERANCE = ', round( 1/(1 - reg02.rsquared), 3 ) )"
   ]

    "##\n",
    "## calculate VIFs\n",
    "##\n",
    "## first create a list of names in the order shown in the scatter plot matrix\n",
    "##\n",
    "indepvars = [ 'GNPDEFL', 'GNP', 'UNEMP', 'ARMED', 'POP', 'YEAR' ]\n",
    "##\n",
    "## invert the correlation matrix and extract the main diaginal\n",
    "##\n",
    "x = np.diag( np.linalg.inv( corr_matrix ) ) \n",
    "##\n",
    "## zip the variable names and the VIFs\n",
    "##\n",
    "xzip = zip( indepvars, x ) \n",
    "##\n",
    "## display the zip matrix\n",
    "##\n",
    "lzip( xzip )"
   ]

    "##\n",
    "## Monthly data for the period January 1983 through May 1990\n",
    "##    Q = shipments of sealing compound used in construction in\n",
    "##        gallons/month (Range 90 - 7723)\n",

    "## use the period_range function as pd.period_range( start, end, freq )\n",
    "##\n",
    "df.index = pd.period_range( '1/1/1983', '5/1/1990', freq = 'M')\n",
    "df.head()"
